it has rooms, as well as a campsite

it has a wonderful garden
and in the evening you can enjoy the 3 courses menu
for starters I had a pumpkin soup
and the main course was fish, fries and vegetables
and this was my desert
super delicious with banana
this is the view out of the restaurant
and in the evening you can enjoy the beautiful sunset

stickerText: Cooking eggs and matoke in hot springs
Let's cook eggs and Makote in the hot springs in Uganda
this place is located in semuliki national park in ntandi town
for that we had to go to the female hot springs
because you can only do it here
instead of the male hot springs
which are really near by
it was really hot here
because of the hot steam from the hot springs
but it looks so beautiful
I mean look at this
the temperature can go up to 100 degrees
that's why we are able to cook something here
but of course the temperature depends on the weather
I mean if it's raining the temperature can go a little bit down
after 10 minutes out eggs were ready
we had to wait 20 minutes more for makote
but after everything was done
it was super delicious
and it was time for lunch
after lunch I also wanted to get a quick look to the male hot springs
it also looks really nice
I will see you next time
Bye :)))

stickerText: I'm currently in Rwanda at lake Kivu
and today we will go on a bicycle tour
actually it was more Mountainbiking than with a normal bike
and I'm not used to it at all
so most of the time it was going up hill
so I had to walk
but at least it was a beautiful view
suddenly
there was like I don't know how to describe it but you can see it
there was no road
so there were some gentlemen they carried our bikes
and we walked
yeah I guess it was because of the thunderstorms
the last days we had so much rain and storms
so yeah one part of the road broke down
yeah this is me enjoying the view it was beautiful
and I was so exhausted
it was such a long trip
but I enjoyed it
Bye :)
